      "label": "Condition",
      "value": "Only at the top of the papyrus is the original cutting line still visible. The text on the recto consists of twelve lines written in black ink parallel to the fibres except the last two lines which are written in the right margin. The handwriting is different from the recto and has been executed in black ink that has disappeared in several places.\nThe text is incomplete on the left, top and bottom sides, which points to the conclusion that it was written before the text on the verso which is complete."
